Simple script to change the charset and collation of the text fields in a mysql database.

How to use:

Just fill in the db details in the variables:

DBHOST='127.0.0.1'
DBUSER='root'
DBPASS=''
DBDB='n_demot'


also the required charset and collation:

CHARSET = 'utf8'
COLLATION = 'utf8_general_ci'
